6	tables	public.production_runs	public.production_runs	Table · 600 rows	# public.production_runs\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThe `production_runs` table has 11 columns and 600 rows. It has foreign keys to `public.operators.operator_id` (via `operator_id`).\n\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-19, model=deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3.1 -->\n## What this table represents\nTracks individual manufacturing production runs, including batch details, timing, output quantities, and status on specific assembly lines.\n\n## Common joins\n- `JOIN public.deviations d ON d.run_id = pr.run_id` (from queries 4-7)\n- `JOIN public.operators ON public.operators.operator_id = pr.operator_id` (inferred from FK)\n\n## Column meanings\n- `run_id` — Unique identifier for each production run\n- `line_id` — Manufacturing line identifier (LINE-A through LINE-D)\n- `batch_id` — Unique batch identifier with date encoding\n- `product_sku` — Product stock keeping unit being manufactured\n- `operator_id` — Identifier of the operator responsible for the run\n- `started_at` — Timestamp when the production run began\n- `ended_at` — Timestamp when the production run completed or aborted\n- `units_target` — Target number of units to produce\n- `units_produced` — Actual number of units produced\n- `status` — Run status: completed, aborted, or test\n- `notes` — Optional notes about the run (always null in this dataset)\n\n## Likely filter patterns\n- `WHERE line_id = 'LINE-A'` (specific production line)\n- `WHERE status = 'completed' AND units_produced < 0.9 * units_target` (failed runs by efficiency threshold)\n- `WHERE started_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'` (recent runs)\n- `WHERE ended_at IS NULL OR ended_at > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` (currently active runs)\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type | Null rate | Distinct | PK | FK |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `run_id` | bigint | 0.0% | 600 | ✓ |  |\n| `line_id` | text | 0.0% | 4 |  |  |\n| `batch_id` | text | 0.0% | 600 |  |  |\n| `product_sku` | text | 0.0% | 6 |  |  |\n| `operator_id` | integer | 0.0% | 8 |  | public.operators.operator_id |\n| `started_at` | timestamp with time zone | 0.0% | 600 |  |  |\n| `ended_at` | timestamp with time zone | 0.0% | 600 |  |  |\n| `units_target` | integer | 0.0% | 300 |  |  |\n| `units_produced` | integer | 0.0% | 366 |  |  |\n| `status` | text | 0.0% | 3 |  |  |\n| `notes` | text | 100.0% | 0 |  |  |\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `run_id` (bigint)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 600\n- Min: `1`\n- Max: `600`\n- Top values:\n  - `354` (1)\n  - `75` (1)\n  - `497` (1)\n  - `551` (1)\n  - `537` (1)\n- Histogram (10 bins): 1:60, 10:60, 2:60, 3:60, 4:60, 5:60, 6:60, 7:60, 8:60, 9:60\n- Sample values: `1`, `10`, `100`, `101`, `102`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `line_id` (text)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 4\n- Min: `LINE-A`\n- Max: `LINE-D`\n- Top values:\n  - `LINE-A` (150)\n  - `LINE-C` (150)\n  - `LINE-D` (150)\n  - `LINE-B` (150)\n- Sample values: `LINE-A`, `LINE-B`, `LINE-C`, `LINE-D`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `batch_id` (text)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 600\n- Min: `B-20260317-0038`\n- Max: `B-20260516-0551`\n- Top values:\n  - `B-20260410-0410` (1)\n  - `B-20260418-0355` (1)\n  - `B-20260419-0239` (1)\n  - `B-20260415-0493` (1)\n  - `B-20260513-0127` (1)\n- Sample values: `B-20260317-0038`, `B-20260317-0132`, `B-20260317-0225`, `B-20260317-0322`, `B-20260317-0385`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `product_sku` (text)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 6\n- Min: `SKU-1001`\n- Max: `SKU-3050`\n- Top values:\n  - `SKU-2010` (100)\n  - `SKU-1001` (100)\n  - `SKU-3050` (100)\n  - `SKU-2011` (100)\n  - `SKU-1003` (100)\n- Sample values: `SKU-1001`, `SKU-1002`, `SKU-1003`, `SKU-2010`, `SKU-2011`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `operator_id` (integer)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 8\n- Min: `1`\n- Max: `8`\n- Top values:\n  - `5` (96)\n  - `3` (92)\n  - `7`