7	tables	public.quality_checks	public.quality_checks	Table · 2452 rows	# public.quality_checks\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThe `quality_checks` table has 8 columns and 2.5k rows. It has foreign keys to `public.production_runs.run_id` (via `run_id`).\n\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-19, model=deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3.1 -->\n## What this table represents\nThis table stores quality control measurements taken during production runs, tracking parameters like viscosity, fill volume, and net weight against their specification limits. Each row represents a single check of a manufacturing parameter to determine if it falls within acceptable bounds.\n\n## Common joins\n- `JOIN public.production_runs ON quality_checks.run_id = production_runs.run_id` (inferred from foreign key)\n\n## Column meanings\n- `check_id` — Unique identifier for each quality check measurement.\n- `run_id` — References the production run during which this check was performed.\n- `checked_at` — Timestamp when the quality measurement was taken.\n- `parameter` — Type of quality parameter being measured (e.g., viscosity_cp, fill_volume_ml).\n- `value` — Measured numeric value of the parameter.\n- `lower_spec` — Minimum acceptable value for this parameter.\n- `upper_spec` — Maximum acceptable value for this parameter.\n- `in_spec` — Boolean indicating whether the measured value falls within the specification limits.\n\n## Likely filter patterns\n- `WHERE parameter = 'viscosity_cp'` (most frequent parameter)\n- `WHERE in_spec = false` (to identify failing checks)\n- `WHERE checked_at BETWEEN '2026-04-01' AND '2026-04-30'` (time-bound analysis)\n- `WHERE value < lower_spec OR value > upper_spec` (explicit out-of-spec filtering)\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type | Null rate | Distinct | PK | FK |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `check_id` | bigint | 0.0% | 2452 | ✓ |  |\n| `run_id` | bigint | 0.0% | 600 |  | public.production_runs.run_id |\n| `checked_at` | timestamp with time zone | 0.0% | 2452 |  |  |\n| `parameter` | text | 0.0% | 5 |  |  |\n| `value` | numeric | 0.0% | 2409 |  |  |\n| `lower_spec` | numeric | 0.0% | 5 |  |  |\n| `upper_spec` | numeric | 0.0% | 5 |  |  |\n| `in_spec` | boolean | 0.0% | 2 |  |  |\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `check_id` (bigint)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 2452\n- Min: `1`\n- Max: `2452`\n- Top values:\n  - `877` (1)\n  - `247` (1)\n  - `121` (1)\n  - `1521` (1)\n  - `1593` (1)\n- Histogram (10 bins): 1:246, 10:246, 2:245, 3:245, 4:245, 5:245, 6:245, 7:245, 8:245, 9:245\n- Sample values: `1`, `10`, `100`, `1000`, `1001`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `run_id` (bigint)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 600\n- Min: `1`\n- Max: `600`\n- Top values:\n  - `34` (6)\n  - `75` (6)\n  - `537` (6)\n  - `247` (6)\n  - `115` (6)\n- Histogram (10 bins): 1:239, 10:277, 2:244, 3:246, 4:254, 5:240, 6:242, 7:245, 8:223, 9:242\n- Sample values: `1`, `10`, `100`, `101`, `102`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `checked_at` (timestamp with time zone)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 2452\n- Min: `2026-03-17 06:24:18.232369+00`\n- Max: `2026-05-17 04:30:01.42472+00`\n- Top values:\n  - `2026-03-22 23:47:07.968299+00` (1)\n  - `2026-03-21 06:08:14.954376+00` (1)\n  - `2026-03-24 08:14:44.222737+00` (1)\n  - `2026-03-18 23:55:27.96309+00` (1)\n  - `2026-04-24 23:32:09.356116+00` (1)\n- Sample values: `2026-03-17 06:24:18.232369+00`, `2026-03-17 06:49:04.577471+00`, `2026-03-17 06:55:26.637674+00`, `2026-03-17 07:06:37.373914+00`, `2026-03-17 07:14:01.427334+00`\n\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n### `parameter` (text)\n\n- Null rate: 0.0%\n- Distinct values: 5\n- Min: `cap_torque_nm`\n- Max: `viscosity_cp`\n- Top values:\n  - `viscosity_cp` (515)\n  - `label_offset_mm` (502)\n  - `fill_volume_ml` (496)\n  - `net_weight_g` (490)\n  - `cap_torque_nm` (449)\n- Sample values: `cap_torque_nm`, `fill_volume_ml`, `label_offset_mm`, `net_weight_g`, `viscosity_cp`\n\n\n<!-- pr