34	tables	loom_views.v_equipment_failure_rates_by_line_90d	loom_views.v_equipment_failure_rates_by_line_90d  (view)	Saved view · 10 rows	# loom_views.v_equipment_failure_rates_by_line_90d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 10 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nEquipment failure rates and severity distribution by production line for the last 90 days (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Identifies problematic equipment and lines for maintenance prioritization and operational improvements)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT e.line_id, e.equipment_id, e.name, COUNT(d.deviation_id) AS total_deviations, SUM(CASE WHEN d.severity = 'critical' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS critical_count, SUM(CASE WHEN d.severity = 'high' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS high_count, ROUND(COUNT(d.deviation_id) * 100.0 / COUNT(pr.run_id), 2) AS deviation_rate_percent FROM public.equipment e JOIN public.deviations d ON e.equipment_id = d.equipment_id JOIN public.production_runs pr ON d.run_id = pr.run_id WHERE d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days' GROUP BY e.line_id, e.equipment_id, e.name ORDER BY total_deviations DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `equipment_id` | integer |\n| `name` | text |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `critical_count` | bigint |\n| `high_count` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate_percent` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_equipment_failure_rates_by_line_90d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1512}	66834c84bf9c1a6d23299a500cf68673	ready	2026-05-17 20:14:01.669516+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.902929+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.669516+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.669516+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
56	code	jsonschema-spec-ietf	jsonschema-spec / ietf	This module defines the IETF RFC document that registers official media types for JSON Schema resources, specifically `application/schema+json` for schemas and `application/schema-instance+json` for i	## What this module does\nThis module defines the IETF RFC document that registers official media types for JSON Schema resources, specifically `application/schema+json` for schemas and `application/schema-instance+json` for instances. It provides the formal specification and rationale for these media types to be entered into the IANA registry.\n\n## Public surface\n*   The primary output is the RFC document itself, which is the authoritative source for the media type registrations.\n*   The defined media types: `application/schema+json` and `application/schema-instance+json`.\n\n## Dependencies & data\n*   Normative references include `RFC9110` (HTTP), `RFC8259` (JSON), `RFC6901` (JSON-Pointer), and `RFC3987` (IRI).\n*   Informative references include prior JSON Schema drafts (`draft-2020-12`, `draft-2019-09`, `draft-07`, `draft-03`).\n\n## When to reference\n*   When implementing a system that needs to correctly identify or serve JSON Schema documents over HTTP and must use the official, IANA-registered media types.\n*   When clarifying the distinction between a JSON Schema document and a JSON instance document in a protocol or API specification.	{"files": ["ietf/json-schema-media-types.md"], "module": "ietf", "code_source_id": 2}	2326f55e9c125b20acd1c1af8ceba0d8	ready	2026-05-19 19:14:40.952678+00	2026-05-19 19:14:40.952678+00	2026-05-19 19:14:40.952678+00	2026-05-19 19:14:40.952678+00	\N	source	code	\N	\N
11	tables	loom_views.v_production_runs_36c23c	loom_views.v_production_runs_36c23c  (view)	Saved view · 12 rows	# loom_views.v_production_runs_36c23c\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 12 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "Which pharma company is leading in antibiotics"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nWITH production_summary AS (\n    SELECT \n        pr.product_sku,\n        pr.line_id,\n        COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id) as total_runs,\n        SUM(pr.units_produced) as total_units,\n        AVG(pr.units_produced::float / NULLIF(pr.units_target, 0)) as avg_efficiency,\n        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN d.category = 'contamination' THEN d.deviation_id END) as contamination_deviations,\n        COUNT(DISTINCT d.deviation_id) as total_deviations\n    FROM public.production_runs pr\n    LEFT JOIN public.deviations d ON pr.run_id = d.run_id\n    WHERE pr.status = 'completed'\n    GROUP BY pr.product_sku, pr.line_id\n)\nSELECT \n    product_sku,\n    line_id,\n    total_runs,\n    total_units,\n    avg_efficiency,\n    contamination_deviations,\n    total_deviations,\n    CASE \n        WHEN total_runs > 0 THEN contamination_deviations::numeric / total_runs\n        ELSE 0 \n    END as contamination_rate\nFROM production_summary\nORDER BY total_units DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `product_sku` | text |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `total_runs` | bigint |\n| `total_units` | bigint |\n| `avg_efficiency` | double precision |\n| `contamination_deviations` | bigint |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `contamination_rate` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_production_runs_36c23c", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 665}	694dbc5d5a1d28ff9b6550a800bb6d82	ready	2026-05-16 19:31:28.384524+00	2026-05-20 08