24	tables	loom_views.v_deviations_13770b	loom_views.v_deviations_13770b  (view)	Saved view · 17 rows	# loom_views.v_deviations_13770b\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 17 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "What's the quality deviation trend this month?"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT\n  date_trunc('day', observed_at) AS day,\n  COUNT(*) AS total_deviations,\n  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value) AS mismatched_values,\n  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) AS deviation_rate\nFROM public.deviations\nWHERE observed_at >= '2026-05-01'  -- Start of current month\n  AND observed_at < '2026-06-01'   -- Start of next month\nGROUP BY date_trunc('day', observed_at)\nORDER BY day\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `day` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatched_values` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate` | double precision |\n\n	{"name": "v_deviations_13770b", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 809}	ba812deee82eccb9d9d3ed2efc5d1720	ready	2026-05-16 20:31:05.220219+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.873891+00	2026-05-16 20:31:05.220219+00	2026-05-16 20:31:05.220219+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
25	tables	loom_views.v_deviations_438794	loom_views.v_deviations_438794  (view)	Saved view · 1 rows	# loom_views.v_deviations_438794\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 1 row as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "What's the quality deviation trend this month?"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nWITH monthly_stats AS (\n  SELECT\n    COUNT(*) AS total_deviations,\n    COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value) AS mismatched_values,\n    COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) AS overall_deviation_rate,\n    AVG(CASE WHEN actual_value <> expected_value THEN 1.0 ELSE 0.0 END) AS avg_deviation_rate,\n    MIN(observed_at) AS first_deviation,\n    MAX(observed_at) AS last_deviation\n  FROM public.deviations\n  WHERE observed_at >= '2026-05-01'\n    AND observed_at < '2026-06-01'\n)\nSELECT \n  total_deviations,\n  mismatched_values,\n  ROUND((overall_deviation_rate * 100)::numeric, 1) AS overall_deviation_rate_percent,\n  ROUND((avg_deviation_rate * 100)::numeric, 1) AS avg_deviation_rate_percent,\n  first_deviation,\n  last_deviation,\n  EXTRACT(DAY FROM last_deviation - first_deviation) + 1 AS days_with_data\nFROM monthly_stats\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatched_values` | bigint |\n| `overall_deviation_rate_percent` | numeric |\n| `avg_deviation_rate_percent` | numeric |\n| `first_deviation` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `last_deviation` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `days_with_data` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_deviations_438794", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 810}	e13280d620cdcadfca4af7adafeffac7	ready	2026-05-16 20:31:05.221696+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.878778+00	2026-05-16 20:31:05.221696+00	2026-