43	tables	loom_views.v_production_runs_3918fe	loom_views.v_production_runs_3918fe  (view)	Saved view · 1 rows	# loom_views.v_production_runs_3918fe\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 1 row as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "How many production runs were failed in the last 30 days?"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    COUNT(*) as total_completed_runs,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN units_produced < 0.9 * units_target THEN 1 END) as failed_runs,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN units_produced >= 0.9 * units_target THEN 1 END) as successful_runs,\n    ROUND(AVG(units_produced::numeric / units_target * 100), 2) as avg_efficiency_percent,\n    MIN(units_produced::numeric / units_target * 100) as min_efficiency_percent,\n    MAX(units_produced::numeric / units_target * 100) as max_efficiency_percent\nFROM public.production_runs\nWHERE started_at >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '30 days'\n  AND status = 'completed'\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `total_completed_runs` | bigint |\n| `failed_runs` | bigint |\n| `successful_runs` | bigint |\n| `avg_efficiency_percent` | numeric |\n| `min_efficiency_percent` | numeric |\n| `max_efficiency_percent` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_production_runs_3918fe", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1565}	2e6a2eb907e62c0d4580942b854a643f	ready	2026-05-17 20:23:40.938941+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.927665+00	2026-05-17 20:23:40.938941+00	2026-05-17 20:23:40.938941+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
