30	tables	loom_views.v_line_performance_last_30d	loom_views.v_line_performance_last_30d  (view)	Saved view · 4 rows	# loom_views.v_line_performance_last_30d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 4 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nAggregates production performance metrics for each line over the last 30 days, including total runs, units produced, and average production rate. (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Provides a high-level summary of output and efficiency for each production line, essential for daily/weekly performance reviews.)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nWITH recent_runs AS (SELECT * FROM public.production_runs WHERE started_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days' AND status = 'completed') SELECT line_id, COUNT(run_id) AS total_runs, SUM(units_produced) AS units_produced, SUM(units_target) AS units_target, ROUND(SUM(units_produced) * 100.0 / NULLIF(SUM(units_target), 0), 2) AS target_achievement_pct, AVG(EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (ended_at - started_at)) / 60.0) AS avg_run_duration_minutes FROM recent_runs GROUP BY line_id ORDER BY line_id\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `total_runs` | bigint |\n| `units_produced` | bigint |\n| `units_target` | bigint |\n| `target_achievement_pct` | numeric |\n| `avg_run_duration_minutes` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_line_performance_last_30d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1121}	86c161b9f0abdc101471bfc4c8ebbb6d	ready	2026-05-17 02:01:15.982577+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.917122+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.982577+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.982577+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
40	tables	loom_views.v_production_runs_e8695f	loom_views.v_production_runs_e8695f  (view)	Saved view · 2 rows	# loom_views.v_production_runs_e8695f\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 2 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "How do we define a failed production run?"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    status,\n    COUNT(*) as total_runs,\n    COUNT(CASE WHEN units_produced < 0.9 * units_target THEN 1 END) as failed_by_90pct_rule,\n    ROUND(100.0 * COUNT(CASE WHEN units_produced < 0.9 * units_target THEN 1 END) / COUNT(*), 1) as failure_rate_pct\nFROM public.production_runs\nWHERE status IN ('completed', 'aborted')\nGROUP BY status\nORDER BY status\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `status` | text |\n| `total_runs` | bigint |\n| `failed_by_90pct_rule` | bigint |\n| `failure_rate_pct` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_production_runs_e8695f", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1552}	303e92d50bcb52dc4b7a01a3c11fc8fc	ready	2026-05-17 20:21:41.435018+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.934122+00	2026-05-17 20:21:41.435018+00	2026-05-17 20:21:41.435018+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
