50	tables	loom_views.v_deviations_101b51	loom_views.v_deviations_101b51  (view)	Saved view · 8 rows	# loom_views.v_deviations_101b51\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 8 rows as of 2026-05-18.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-18 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "What should i do to fix this?"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n  pr.operator_id,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) as total_deviations,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) FILTER (WHERE d.actual_value <> d.expected_value) as mismatch_deviations,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) FILTER (WHERE d.actual_value <> d.expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(d.deviation_id), 0) as mismatch_rate,\n  COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id) as total_runs,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id), 0) as deviations_per_run\nFROM public.deviations d\nJOIN public.production_runs pr ON d.run_id = pr.run_id\nWHERE d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'\n  AND pr.line_id = 'LINE-B'\nGROUP BY pr.operator_id\nORDER BY mismatch_rate DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `operator_id` | integer |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatch_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatch_rate` | double precision |\n| `total_runs` | bigint |\n| `deviations_per_run` | double precision |\n\n	{"name": "v_deviations_101b51", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 2145}	d1e7071e4e521de8e4dc06012d58ff07	ready	2026-05-18 06:21:21.6248+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.872635+00	2026-05-18 06:21:21.6248+00	2026-05-18 06:21:21.6248+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
