19	tables	loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_severity_90d	loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_severity_90d  (view)	Saved view · 40 rows	# loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_severity_90d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 40 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nEquipment deviation counts by severity level for the last 90 days (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Equipment maintenance teams need to identify which equipment is generating the most severe deviations to prioritize maintenance and repairs)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT e.equipment_id, e.name, e.line_id, d.severity, COUNT(d.deviation_id) as deviation_count FROM public.deviations d JOIN public.equipment e ON d.equipment_id = e.equipment_id WHERE d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days' GROUP BY e.equipment_id, e.name, e.line_id, d.severity\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `equipment_id` | integer |\n| `name` | text |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `severity` | text |\n| `deviation_count` | bigint |\n\n	{"name": "v_equipment_deviation_severity_90d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 776}	2f632a182cd298e5d79ba6aff640ad41	ready	2026-05-16 20:06:01.506476+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.899197+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.506476+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.506476+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
29	tables	loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_summary_30d	loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_summary_30d  (view)	Saved view · 10 rows	# loom_views.v_equipment_deviation_summary_30d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 10 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nShows deviation volume and severity per piece of equipment over the last 30 days, linked to equipment location (line) for failure hotspot analysis. (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Identifies problematic equipment by line and severity, crucial for maintenance prioritization and root cause analysis.)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT e.equipment_id, e.name, e.line_id, e.manufacturer, COUNT(d.deviation_id) AS total_deviations, SUM(CASE WHEN d.severity IN ('critical', 'high') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS high_severity_count, MIN(d.observed_at) AS first_deviation_date, MAX(d.observed_at) AS last_deviation_date, SUM(CASE WHEN d.resolved_at IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS unresolved_count FROM public.equipment e LEFT JOIN public.deviations d ON e.equipment_id = d.equipment_id AND d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days' GROUP BY e.equipment_id, e.name, e.line_id, e.manufacturer ORDER BY total_deviations DESC NULLS LAST\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `equipment_id` | integer |\n| `name` | text |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `manufacturer` | text |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `high_severity_count` | bigint |\n| `first_deviation_date` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `last_deviation_date` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `unresolved_count` | bigint |\n\n	{"name": "v_equipment_deviation_summary_30d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1122}	71e19fc8888adaeef96165d6148df12d	ready	2026-05-17 02:01:15.977449+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.900046+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.977449+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.977449+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
27	tables	loom_views.v_deviation_trend_daily_current_month	loom_views.v_deviation_trend_daily_current_month  (view)	Saved view · 17 rows	# loom_views.v_deviation_trend_daily_current_month\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 17 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nDaily deviation trend for the current month, showing total deviations, mismatched values, and deviation rate percentage\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT\n  date_trunc('day', observed_at) AS day,\n  COUNT(*) AS total_deviations,\n  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value) AS mismatched_values,\n  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) AS deviation_rate,\n  ROUND((COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE actual_value <> expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) * 100)::numeric, 1) AS deviation_rate_percent\nFROM public.deviations\nWHERE observed_at >= date_trunc('month', CURRENT_DATE)\n  AND observed_at < date_trunc('month', CURRENT_DATE) + INTERVAL '1 month'\nGROUP BY date_trunc('day', observed_at)\nORDER BY day\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `day` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatched_values` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate` | double precision |\n| `deviation_rate_percent` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_deviation_trend_daily_current_month", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 808}	058ef7759d38233891cc9fd4fb2efbc8	ready	2026-05-16 20:31:05.226304+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.892872+00	2026-05-16 20:31:05.226304+00	2026-05-16 20:31:05.226304+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
