32	tables	loom_views.v_quality_summary_weekly	loom_views.v_quality_summary_weekly  (view)	Saved view · 45 rows	# loom_views.v_quality_summary_weekly\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 45 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nA time-series view of quality check pass rates and out-of-spec count aggregated by week and parameter for trending. (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Enables trend analysis of quality performance over time for each measurement parameter.)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT DATE_TRUNC('week', q.checked_at) AS week_start, q.parameter, COUNT(q.check_id) AS total_checks, SUM(CASE WHEN q.in_spec THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS in_spec_count, ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN q.in_spec THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(q.check_id), 2) AS in_spec_rate_pct, SUM(CASE WHEN q.in_spec = FALSE THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS out_of_spec_count FROM public.quality_checks q WHERE q.checked_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days' GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('week', q.checked_at), q.parameter ORDER BY week_start DESC, q.parameter\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `week_start` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `parameter` | text |\n| `total_checks` | bigint |\n| `in_spec_count` | bigint |\n| `in_spec_rate_pct` | numeric |\n| `out_of_spec_count` | bigint |\n\n	{"name": "v_quality_summary_weekly", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1123}	746b111dff6805c43ccac1607494031b	ready	2026-05-17 02:01:15.994395+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.939645+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.994395+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.994395+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
38	tables	loom_views.v_deviation_rate_by_line_30d_current	loom_views.v_deviation_rate_by_line_30d_current  (view)	Saved view · 4 rows	# loom_views.v_deviation_rate_by_line_30d_current\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 4 rows as of 2026-05-18.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-18 -->\n## What this view represents\nDeviation rate by production line for the last 30 days, calculated as deviations with mismatched values divided by total deviations\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nWITH deviation_data AS (\n  SELECT \n    pr.line_id,\n    d.observed_at,\n    d.expected_value,\n    d.actual_value,\n    CASE WHEN d.actual_value <> d.expected_value THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_mismatch\n  FROM public.deviations d\n  JOIN public.production_runs pr ON d.run_id = pr.run_id\n  WHERE d.observed_at >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '30 days'\n)\nSELECT \n  line_id,\n  COUNT(*) AS total_deviations,\n  SUM(is_mismatch) AS deviations_with_mismatch,\n  SUM(is_mismatch)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*), 0) AS deviation_rate\nFROM deviation_data\nGROUP BY line_id\nORDER BY deviation_rate DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `deviations_with_mismatch` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate` | double precision |\n\n	{"name": "v_deviation_rate_by_line_30d_current", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1515}	7d6b5e5a7faa9f9785b4d6587505d351	ready	2026-05-18 05:57:20.517272+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.870424+00	2026-05-17 20:14:40.920108+00	2026-05-18 05:57:20.517272+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
37	tables	loom_views.v_weekly_deviation_summary_30d	loom_views.v_weekly_deviation_summary_30d  (view)	Saved view · 94 rows	# loom_views.v_weekly_deviation_summary_30d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 94 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nWeekly counts of production deviations by category and severity, including average time to resolution for resolved cases in the last 30 days (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Helps track frequency and impact of production anomalies over time, showing trends and resolution performance)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nWITH deviations_with_week AS (SELECT d.*, DATE_TRUNC('week', d.observed_at) AS week_start, EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM (d.resolved_at - d.observed_at)) / 3600 AS hours_to_resolve FROM public.deviations d WHERE d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days') SELECT week_start, category, severity, COUNT(*) AS deviation_count, AVG(hours_to_resolve) FILTER (WHERE resolved_at IS NOT NULL) AS avg_hours_to_resolve FROM deviations_with_week GROUP BY week_start, category, severity ORDER BY week_start DESC, deviation_count DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `week_start` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `category` | text |\n| `severity` | text |\n| `deviation_count` | bigint |\n| `avg_hours_to_resolve` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_weekly_deviation_summary_30d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1511}	42aa05145ad144a68d031fe6284f0dc2	ready	2026-05-17 20:14:01.682838+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.942178+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.682838+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.682838+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
21	tables	loom_views.v_quality_check_failure_rate_30d	loom_views.v_quality_check_failure_rate_30d  (view)	Saved view · 5 rows	# loom_views.v_quality_check_failure_rate_30d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 5 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nQuality check failure rates by parameter for the last 30 days (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Quality teams need to monitor which parameters are failing most frequently to focus improvement efforts on critical quality issues)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT qc.parameter, COUNT(qc.check_id) as total_checks, SUM(CASE WHEN qc.in_spec = false THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as failed_checks, SUM(CASE WHEN qc.in_spec = false THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)::numeric / COUNT(qc.check_id) as failure_rate FROM public.quality_checks qc WHERE qc.checked_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days' GROUP BY qc.parameter\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `parameter` | text |\n| `total_checks` | bigint |\n| `failed_checks` | bigint |\n| `failure_rate` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_quality_check_failure_rate_30d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 778}	f8a0c02139873b8592e9e1c3d66ca316	ready	2026-05-16 20:06:01.517852+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.937351+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.517852+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.517852+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
