49	tables	loom_views.v_equipment_e45131	loom_views.v_equipment_e45131  (view)	Saved view · 2 rows	# loom_views.v_equipment_e45131\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 2 rows as of 2026-05-18.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-18 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "Nono just equiments"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n  e.equipment_id,\n  e.name,\n  e.manufacturer,\n  e.installed_at,\n  e.last_maintenance_at,\n  e.next_maintenance_due,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) as total_deviations,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) FILTER (WHERE d.actual_value <> d.expected_value) as mismatch_deviations,\n  COUNT(d.deviation_id) FILTER (WHERE d.actual_value <> d.expected_value)::float / NULLIF(COUNT(d.deviation_id), 0) as mismatch_rate\nFROM public.equipment e\nLEFT JOIN public.deviations d ON e.equipment_id = d.equipment_id\n  AND d.observed_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'\nWHERE e.line_id = 'LINE-B'\nGROUP BY e.equipment_id, e.name, e.manufacturer, e.installed_at, e.last_maintenance_at, e.next_maintenance_due\nORDER BY total_deviations DESC NULLS LAST\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `equipment_id` | integer |\n| `name` | text |\n| `manufacturer` | text |\n| `installed_at` | date |\n| `last_maintenance_at` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `next_maintenance_due` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `total_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatch_deviations` | bigint |\n| `mismatch_rate` | double precision |\n\n	{"name": "v_equipment_e45131", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 2136}	f9660da60cd2ec533af7c8b66521ebe6	ready	2026-05-18 06:20:21.668304+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.901603+00	2026-05-18 06:20:21.668304+00	2026-05-18 06:20:21.668304+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
13	tables	loom_views.v_production_runs_b7db96	loom_views.v_production_runs_b7db96  (view)	Saved view · 12 rows	# loom_views.v_production_runs_b7db96\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 12 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "Which pharma company is leading in antibiotics"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    pr.product_sku,\n    d.category,\n    COUNT(DISTINCT d.deviation_id) as contamination_deviations,\n    COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id) as total_runs,\n    ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT d.deviation_id)::numeric / COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id)::numeric, 3) as deviation_rate\nFROM public.production_runs pr\nLEFT JOIN public.deviations d ON pr.run_id = d.run_id AND d.category = 'contamination'\nWHERE pr.status = 'completed'\nGROUP BY pr.product_sku, d.category\nORDER BY contamination_deviations DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `product_sku` | text |\n| `category` | text |\n| `contamination_deviations` | bigint |\n| `total_runs` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_production_runs_b7db96", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 664}	49549d3a6c4a44e623efa2ef6a9c5b51	ready	2026-05-16 19:31:28.387495+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.932734+00	2026-05-16 19:31:28.387495+00	2026-05-16 19:31:28.387495+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
