57	code	jsonschema-spec-specs	jsonschema-spec / specs	This module contains the core specification documents and proposals that define the JSON Schema language. It specifies the formal rules for validating and annotating JSON documents, including the core	## What this module does\nThis module contains the core specification documents and proposals that define the JSON Schema language. It specifies the formal rules for validating and annotating JSON documents, including the core data model, the validation vocabulary, the machine-readable output format, and experimental keyword proposals.\n\n## Public surface\n- `jsonschema-core.md` defines the foundational concepts, instance data model, and abstract evaluation model.\n- `jsonschema-validation.md` defines the standard validation keywords (e.g., `type`, `properties`, `required`).\n- `output/jsonschema-validation-output-machines.md` specifies the standard format for validation results and annotations.\n- `proposals/propertyDependencies.md` and `proposals/propertyDependencies-adr.md` document the proposed `propertyDependencies` keyword for schema selection based on property values.\n\n## Dependencies & data\n- The specifications reference RFC 2119 for conformance language ("MUST", "SHOULD", etc.).\n- They are designed to be platform-independent and do not reference external libraries or specific data tables.\n\n## When to reference\n- When you need to understand the formal validation rules or output format for a JSON Schema implementation.\n- When designing a schema that requires conditional validation based on a property's value and evaluating the proposed `propertyDependencies` keyword.\n- When contributing to the JSON Schema specification itself or authoring a compatible validator.	{"files": ["specs/jsonschema-core.md", "specs/jsonschema-validation.md", "specs/meta/README.md", "specs/output/jsonschema-validation-output-machines.md", "specs/proposals/propertyDependencies-adr.md", "specs/proposals/propertyDependencies.md", "specs/proposals/proposal-template.md", "specs/proposals/vocabularies-adr.md", "specs/proposals/vocabularies.md"], "module": "specs", "code_source_id": 2}	68151ad3c518d5f053dd1a4cd4443103	ready	2026-05-19 19:14:52.145224+00	2026-05-19 19:14:52.145224+00	2026-05-19 19:14:52.145224+00	2026-05-19 19:14:52.145224+00	\N	source	code	\N	\N
