41	tables	loom_views.v_failed_production_runs_30d	loom_views.v_failed_production_runs_30d  (view)	Saved view · 291 rows	# loom_views.v_failed_production_runs_30d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 291 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nShows all completed production runs from the last 30 days with their efficiency percentage and failure status based on the 90% threshold rule\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    run_id,\n    line_id,\n    batch_id,\n    product_sku,\n    operator_id,\n    started_at,\n    ended_at,\n    units_target,\n    units_produced,\n    ROUND((units_produced::numeric / units_target * 100), 2) as efficiency_percent,\n    CASE \n        WHEN units_produced < 0.9 * units_target THEN 'failed'\n        ELSE 'successful'\n    END as run_status\nFROM public.production_runs\nWHERE started_at >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '30 days'\n  AND status = 'completed'\nORDER BY started_at DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `run_id` | bigint |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `batch_id` | text |\n| `product_sku` | text |\n| `operator_id` | integer |\n| `started_at` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `ended_at` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `units_target` | integer |\n| `units_produced` | integer |\n| `efficiency_percent` | numeric |\n| `run_status` | text |\n\n	{"name": "v_failed_production_runs_30d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1563}	f3ed101028733d3b512c4c3f5aad1778	ready	2026-05-17 20:23:40.930301+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.903785+00	2026-05-17 20:23:40.930301+00	2026-05-17 20:23:40.930301+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
14	tables	loom_views.v_production_runs_fe0280	loom_views.v_production_runs_fe0280  (view)	Saved view · 12 rows	# loom_views.v_production_runs_fe0280\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 12 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nAuto-saved by Loom because the underlying query had aggregation/filters and was likely to be re-asked. Originated from: "Which pharma company is leading in antibiotics"\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT \n    pr.product_sku,\n    pr.line_id,\n    COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id) as run_count,\n    SUM(pr.units_produced) as total_units_produced,\n    AVG(pr.units_produced::float / NULLIF(pr.units_target, 0)) as efficiency_rate\nFROM public.production_runs pr\nWHERE pr.status = 'completed'\nGROUP BY pr.product_sku, pr.line_id\nORDER BY total_units_produced DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `product_sku` | text |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `run_count` | bigint |\n| `total_units_produced` | bigint |\n| `efficiency_rate` | double precision |\n\n	{"name": "v_production_runs_fe0280", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 663}	6fe1c794e23fde730caf31105da7e94f	ready	2026-05-16 19:31:28.388817+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.936455+00	2026-05-16 19:31:28.388817+00	2026-05-16 19:31:28.388817+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
