31	tables	loom_views.v_operator_certified_line_summary	loom_views.v_operator_certified_line_summary  (view)	Saved view · 8 rows	# loom_views.v_operator_certified_line_summary\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 8 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nShows operators with their shift, certifications, and counts of recent completed runs to assess workload and line specialization. (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Links operator certification and shift data to their actual production activity, useful for resource planning and skill matching.)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT o.operator_id, o.full_name, o.shift, o.certified_lines, COUNT(pr.run_id) AS recent_run_count, SUM(pr.units_produced) AS recent_units_produced FROM public.operators o LEFT JOIN public.production_runs pr ON o.operator_id = pr.operator_id AND pr.started_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days' AND pr.status = 'completed' GROUP BY o.operator_id, o.full_name, o.shift, o.certified_lines ORDER BY recent_run_count DESC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `operator_id` | integer |\n| `full_name` | text |\n| `shift` | text |\n| `certified_lines` | ARRAY |\n| `recent_run_count` | bigint |\n| `recent_units_produced` | bigint |\n\n	{"name": "v_operator_certified_line_summary", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1124}	f3b8f4b11bd599c34808ddb7f344eb91	ready	2026-05-17 02:01:15.984057+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.919844+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.984057+00	2026-05-17 02:01:15.984057+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
35	tables	loom_views.v_operator_performance_metrics_90d	loom_views.v_operator_performance_metrics_90d  (view)	Saved view · 8 rows	# loom_views.v_operator_performance_metrics_90d\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 8 rows as of 2026-05-17.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-17 -->\n## What this view represents\nOperator performance metrics including production volume and deviation rates by shift for the last 90 days (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Evaluates operator effectiveness across shifts, helping with workforce management and training allocation)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT o.operator_id, o.full_name, o.shift, COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id) AS run_count, SUM(pr.units_produced) AS total_units_produced, COUNT(d.deviation_id) AS deviation_count, ROUND(COUNT(d.deviation_id) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT pr.run_id), 2) AS deviation_rate_percent FROM public.operators o JOIN public.production_runs pr ON o.operator_id = pr.operator_id LEFT JOIN public.deviations d ON pr.run_id = d.run_id WHERE pr.started_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days' GROUP BY o.operator_id, o.full_name, o.shift ORDER BY total_units_produced DESC, deviation_rate_percent ASC\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `operator_id` | integer |\n| `full_name` | text |\n| `shift` | text |\n| `run_count` | bigint |\n| `total_units_produced` | bigint |\n| `deviation_count` | bigint |\n| `deviation_rate_percent` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_operator_performance_metrics_90d", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 1514}	62b414ee2b2fb0d15b8fcca21b1e1d62	ready	2026-05-17 20:14:01.673759+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.923092+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.673759+00	2026-05-17 20:14:01.673759+00	\N	source	tables	\N	\N
