22	tables	loom_views.v_weekly_production_efficiency	loom_views.v_weekly_production_efficiency  (view)	Saved view · 36 rows	# loom_views.v_weekly_production_efficiency\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\nThis is a **view** created by Loom. 36 rows as of 2026-05-16.\n\n<!-- provenance: claude, 2026-05-16 -->\n## What this view represents\nWeekly production efficiency metrics by production line (auto-seeded by Loom. Reason: Production managers need weekly efficiency trends by line to monitor performance and identify areas for improvement)\n\n## Definition\n\n```sql\nSELECT DATE_TRUNC('week', pr.started_at) as week_start, pr.line_id, COUNT(pr.run_id) as run_count, SUM(pr.units_produced) as total_units, AVG(pr.units_produced::numeric / pr.units_target) as efficiency_rate FROM public.production_runs pr WHERE pr.started_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '12 weeks' AND pr.status = 'completed' GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('week', pr.started_at), pr.line_id\n```\n\n<!-- provenance: schema -->\n## Columns\n\n| Column | Type |\n| --- | --- |\n| `week_start` | timestamp with time zone |\n| `line_id` | text |\n| `run_count` | bigint |\n| `total_units` | bigint |\n| `efficiency_rate` | numeric |\n\n	{"name": "v_weekly_production_efficiency", "schema": "loom_views", "is_view": true, "table_id": 777}	2f1e31d0bc8d3ad981752ba71ec01f5f	ready	2026-05-16 20:06:01.519437+00	2026-05-20 08:54:07.943213+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.519437+00	2026-05-16 20:06:01.519437+00	10	source	tables	\N	\N
